 g strong white bread flour"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g plain yoghurt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"100 g milk, plus extra for sealing"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g vegetable oil, plus extra for greasing"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp caster sugar"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp fine sea salt"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"1 tsp dried instant yeast"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Peshwari Naan Filling"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"75 g blanched almonds"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"25 g desiccated coconut"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"30 g sultanas"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 Tbsp runny honey, for garnish"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 Tbsp flaked almonds, for garnish"}],"nutrition":["per 1 piece","1511 kJ \/ 361 kcal","11.4 g","49.6 g","13.1 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Ungarnished naans can be reheated on the same day by sprinkling with a few drops of water and placing in a hot oven for 5 minutes.","This sweet variation on the classic flatbread contains an almond, coconut and sultana filling – flavours which provide the perfect balance to spiced dishes. This version has become a firm favourite among our curry houses. Best eaten warm."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h","8 pieces"]}